postcontent: I have a Colt SAA with 5.5" barrel and in 357mag for sale. The gun was made in early 2015 and was purchased as new by me. The gun hasn't been shot more than 100x. Overall, a very nice gun.These guns now MSRP for $1799, up from $1599, and cannot really be found NIB. Therefore they hold value.This gun will make a fine grade shooter. Despite the low round count, it does have some minor handling marks on the cylinder from removal and installation, it also has a partial turn ring due to a factory sharp bolt edge and careless handling before my taking possession of it. The bolt head has since been dressed. The only other tiny blem is a small nick in the bottom grip strap. Full disclosure. Now those things may sound terrible, but honestly you don't even notice stuff like that on such a fine six gun. Especially one built and tuned to shoot. $1350 takes it home.
